race.comment: TRUMPER (6) nice type from the Kris Lees' yard gelded over the break. Fitted with the two excellent trials and no surprise to see him finish over the top of these. Tongue-tie goes on and sure to go close. PRECIOUS GIRL (11) comes here in peak form after the two courageous on-pace seconds on the provincial circuit. Andrew Gibbons keeps the ride and will prove hard to run down again over the 900m. APOLLO RIDGE (1) resumed with the two solid trial wins under the belt for a fighting on-speed second over 1000m at Kembla Grange. Gets map favours and shapes as a leading contender. AETERNUM (3) Tassort colt from a Nicconi mare on debut for the Kristen Buchanan yard. Has shown a turn of foot in both trial wins and ticks plenty of boxes.
